    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a clash of interpretations, but doesn't one side at least have more \"objective\" facts to lean on? like, if the stats show that more laws equals less crime, isn't that a more solid foundation for policy than just debating how the constitution should be read? it feels like one side is based on reality and the other is just based on ideology.",
